obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (38276)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38276&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Petroleum Act, 1934.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2***.]`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^3 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `3. 30th March, 1937, Gazette of India, 1937, pt. I, p. 632.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (38277)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38277&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(a) "petroleum" means any liquid hydrocarbon or mixture of hydrocarbons, and any inflammable`
  line `mixture (liquid, viscous or solid) containing any liquid hydrocarbon;`
  line
  line `^1[(b) "petroleum Class A" means petroleum having a flash-point below twenty-three degrees`
  line Centigrade;
  line
  line `(bb) "petroleum Class B" means petroleum having a flash-point of twenty-three degrees`
  line `Centigrade and above but below sixty-five degrees Centigrade;`
  line
  line `(bbb) "petroleum Class C" means petroleum having a flash-point of sixty-five degrees Centigrade`
  line `and above but below ninety-three degree Centigrade;]`
  line
  line `(c)`
  line `^2["flash-point"] of any petroleum means the lowest temperature at which it yields a vapour`
  line `which will give a momentary flash when ignited, determined in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `Chapter II and the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `^3[(d) "to transport petroleum" means to move petroleum from one place to another in India and`
  line `includes moving from one place to another in India across a territory which is not part of India;]`
  line
  line `(e) "to import" petroleum means to bring it into ^4[India] by land, sea or air, otherwise than during`
  line `the course of transport;`
  line
  line `(f) "to store" petroleum means to keep it in any one place, but does not include any detention`
  line `happening during the ordinary course of transport;`
  line
  line `(g) "motor conveyance" means any vehicle, vessel or aircraft for the conveyance of human`
  line `beings, animals or goods, by land, water or air, in which petroleum is used to generate the motive`
  line power;
  line
  line `(h) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1970, s. 3, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "flashing-point" (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause (d) (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Schedule for "the territories to which this Act extends" (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `5. Clause (i) omitted by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule. Earlier inserted by the A.O. 1950.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (38278)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Import, transport and storage of petroleum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1970, s. 4, for "any dangerous petroleum" (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38278&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) No one shall import, transport or store any`
  line `petroleum save in accordance with the rules made under section 4.`
  line
  line `(2) Save in accordance with the conditions of any licence for the purpose which he may be required to`
  line `obtain by rules made under section 4, no one shall import ^1[petroleum Class A], and no one shall transport`
  line `transport or store any petroleum.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (38279)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Rules for the import, transport and storage of petroleum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38279&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[Central Government] may`
  line `makes rules--`
  line
  line `(a) prescribing places where petroleum may be imported and prohibiting its import elsewhere;`
  line
  line `(b) regulating the import of petroleum;`
  line
  line `(c) prescribing the periods within which licences for the import of ^2[petroleum Class A] shall be`
  line `applied for, and providing for the disposal, by confiscation or otherwise, of any ^2[petroleum Class A]`
  line `in respect of which a licence has not been applied for within the prescribed period or has been refused`
  line `and which has not been exported;`
  line
  line `(d) regulating the transport of petroleum;`
  line
  line `(e) specifying the nature and condition of all receptacles and pipe-lines in which petroleum may`
  line `be transported;`
  line
  line `(f) regulating the places at which and prescribing the conditions subject to which petroleum may`
  line `be stored;`
  line
  line `(g) specifying the nature, situation and condition of all receptacles in which petroleum may be`
  line stored;
  line
  line `(h) prescribing the form and conditions of licences for the import of ^2[petroleum Class A], and for`
  line `the transport or storages of any petroleum, the manner in which applications for such licences shall be`
  line
  line `made, the authorities which may grant such licences and the fees which may be charged for such`
  line licences;
  line
  line `(i) determining in any class of cases whether a licence for the transport of petroleum shall be`
  line `obtained by the consignor, consignee or carrier;`
  line
  line `(j) providing for the granting of combined licences for the import, transport and storage of`
  line `petroleum, or for any two of such purposes;`
  line
  line `(k) prescribing the proportion in which any specified poisonous substance may be added to`
  line `petroleum, and prohibiting the import, transport or storage of petroleum in which the proportion of`
  line `any specified poisonous substance exceeds the prescribed proportion; and`
  line
  line `(l) generally, providing for any matter which in ^3[its] opinion is expedient for proper control over`
  line `the import, transport and storage of petroleum ^4[including the charging of fees for any services`
  line `rendered in connection with the import, transport and storage of petroleum].`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Governor-General-in-Council".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 24 of 1970, s. 5, for "dangerous petroleum" (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "his".`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 24 of 1970, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-8-1976)`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (38280)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Production, refining and blending of petroleum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38280&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) No one shall produce, refine or blend`
  line `petroleum save in accordance with the rules made under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) The ^1[Central Government] may makes rules--`
  line
  line `(a) prescribing the conditions subject to which petroleum may be produced, refined or blended;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) regulating the removal of petroleum from places where it is produced, refined or blended and`
  line `preventing the storage therein and removal therefrom, except as ^2[petroleum Class A], of any`
  line `petroleum, which has not satisfied the prescribed tests.`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Governor-General-in-Council".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 24 of 1970, s. 6, for "dangerous petroleum" (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (3) omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (38281)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Receptacles of petroleum Class A to show a warning.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38281&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `All receptacles containing ^1[petroleum`
  line `Class A] shall have a stamped, embossed, painted or printed warning, either on the receptacle itself or,`
  line `where that is impracticable, displayed near the receptacle, exhibiting in conspicuous characters the words`
  line `"Petrol" or "Motor Spirit", or an equivalent warning of the dangerous nature of the petroleum:`
  line
  line `Provided that this section shall not apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) any securely stoppered glass, stoneware or metal receptacle of less than ^2[ten litres] capacity`
  line `containing ^1[petroleum Class A] which is not for sale, or`
  line
  line `(b) a tank incorporated in a motor conveyance, or attached to an internal combustion engine, and`
  line `containing petroleum intended to be used to generate motive power for the motor conveyance or`
  line `engine, or`
  line
  line `(c) a pipe-line for the transport of petroleum, or`
  line
  line `(d) any tank which is wholly underground, or`
  line
  line `(e) any class of receptacles which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, exempt from the operation of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1970, s. 7, for "dangerous petroleum" (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "two gallons" (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (38381)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `No licence needed for transport or storage of limited quantities of petroleum Class B or petroleum Class C.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1970, s. 8, for sections 7 and 8 (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38381&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1[7. No licence needed for transport or storage of limited quantities of petroleum Class B or`
  line `petroleum Class C.--Notwithstanding anything contained in this Chapter, a person need not obtain a`
  line `licence for the transport or storage of--`
  line
  line `(i) petroleum Class B if the total quantity in his possession at any one place does not exceed two`
  line `thousand and five hundred litres and none of it is contained in a receptacle exceeding one thousand`
  line `litres in capacity; or`
  line
  line `(ii) petroleum Class C if the total quantity in his possession at any one place does not exceed`
  line `forty-five thousand litres and such petroleum is transported or stored in accordance with the rules`
  line `made under section 4.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (38283)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `No licence needed for import, transport or storage of small quantities of petroleum Class A.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1970, s. 8, for sections 7 and 8 (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38283&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[8. No licence needed for import, transport or storage of small quantities of petroleum Class`
  line `A.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Chapter, a person need not obtain a licence for the`
  line `import, transport or storage of petroleum Class A not intended for sale if the total quantity in his`
  line `possession does not exceed thirty litres,`
  line
  line `(2) Petroleum Class A possessed without a licence under this section shall be kept in securely`
  line `stoppered receptacles of glass, stoneware or metal which shall not, in the case of receptacles of glass or`
  line `stoneware, exceed one liter in capacity or, in the case of receptacles of metal exceed twenty-five litres in`
  line capacity.]
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (38284)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Exemptions for motor conveyances and stationary engines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38284&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner of a motor`
  line `conveyance, who complies with the requirements of the law for the time being in force relating to the`
  line `registration and licensing of such conveyance and its driver or pilot and the owner of any stationary`
  line `internal combustion engine, shall not be required to obtain a licence--`
  line
  line `(a) for the import, transport or storage of any petroleum contained in any fuel tank incorporated`
  line `in the conveyance or attached to the internal combustion engine, or`
  line
  line `(b) for the transport or storage of ^1[petroleum Class A], not exceeding ^2[one hundred litres] in`
  line `quantity in addition to any quantity possessed under clause (a),`
  line
  line `provided the petroleum is intended to be used to generate motive power for motor conveyance or engine:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that the total quantity of ^1[petroleum Class A] which may be stored without a`
  line `licence under clause (b) shall not exceed ^19[one hundred litres], notwithstanding that such owner may`
  line `possess other motor conveyances or engines.]`
  line
  line `(2)`
  line `^1[Petroleum Class A] transported or stored without a licence under clause (b) ^3[of sub-section (1)]`
  line `shall be kept as provided in sub-section (2) of section 8, and, if it exceeds ^4[thirty litres] in quantity, shall`
  line `be stored in an isolated place which does not communicate with any room where any person resides or`
  line `works or in any room where persons assemble.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for "dangerous petroleum" (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for "twenty gallons" (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 25 of 1940, s. 2`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 24 of 1970, s. 9, for "six gallons" (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (38285)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `No licence needed by railway administration acting as carrier.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38285&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Chapter, a railway administration as defined in section 3 of the Indian Railways Act,`
  line `1890 (9 of 1890) need not obtain any licence for the import or transport of any petroleum in its possession`
  line `in its capacity as carrier.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (38286)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Exemption of heavy oils.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1970, s. 10, for section 11 (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38286&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^1[11. Exemption of heavy oils.--Nothing in this Chapter shall apply to any petroleum which has its`
  line `flash-point not below ninety-three degrees Centigrade.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (38287)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `General power of exemption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Governor-General-in-Council".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38287&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[Central Government] may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, exempt any petroleum specified in the notification from all or any of the provisions of this`
  line Chapter.
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (38288)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Inspection of places.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Governor-General-in-Council".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38288&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[Central Government] may authorise any officer by name or by`
  line `virtue of office to enter any place where petroleum is being imported, stored, produced, refined or`
  line `blended, or is under transport, and inspect all receptacles, plant and appliances used in connection with`
  line `petroleum in order to ascertain if they are in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter and the rules`
  line `made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^1[Central Government] may make rules regulating the procedure of officers authorised under`
  line `this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (38289)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Inspection and sampling of petroleum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Governor-General-in-Council".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38289&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[Central Government] may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, authorise, any officer by name or by virtue of office to enter any place where`
  line `petroleum is being imported, transported, stored, produced, refined or blended and to inspect and take`
  line `samples for testing of any petroleum found therein.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^1[Central Government] may make rules--`
  line
  line `(a) regulating the taking of samples of petroleum for testing;`
  line
  line `(b) determining the cases in which payment shall be made for the value of samples taken, and the`
  line `mode of payment, and`
  line
  line `(c) generally, regulating the procedure of officers exercising powers under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (38290)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Standard Test Apparatus.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38290&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) A standard apparatus for determining the ^2[flash-point] of`
  line `petroleum shall be deposited with an officer to be appointed in this behalf by the ^1[Central Government]`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) Such apparatus shall be engraved with the words "Standard Test Apparatus", and shall be verified`
  line `and corrected from time to time and replaced when necessary, in accordance with rules under section 21.`
  line
  line `(3) The Standard Test Apparatus shall, on payment of the prescribed fee, be open to inspection at all`
  line `reasonable times by any person wishing to inspect it.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Governor-General-in-Council".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 24 of 1970, s. 10, for "flashing-point" (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (38291)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Certification of other test apparatus.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1970, s. 12, for "flashing-point" (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38291&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The officer appointed under section 15 shall, on`
  line `payment of the prescribed fee, if any, compare with the Standard Test Apparatus and apparatus for`
  line `determining the ^1[flash-point] of petroleum which may be submitted to him for this purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) If any apparatus is found by him to agree with the Standard Test Apparatus within prescribed`
  line `limits, the officer shall engrave such apparatus with a special number and with the date of the comparison`
  line `and shall give a certificate in respect of it in the prescribed form, certifying that on the said date the`
  line `apparatus was compared with the Standard Test Apparatus and was found to agree with it within the`
  line `prescribed limits, and specifying any corrections to be made in the results of tests carried out with the`
  line apparatus.
  line
  line `(3) A certificate granted under this section shall be valid for such period as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) A certificate granted under this section shall, during the period for which it is valid, be proof, until`
  line `the contrary is proved, of any matter stated therein.`
  line
  line `(5) The officer shall keep a register in the prescribed form of all certificates granted by him under this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (38292)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Testing officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Governor-General-in-Council".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38292&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[Central Government] may authorise any officer by name or by virtue of`
  line `office to test petroleum of which samples have been taken under this Act, or which may have been`
  line `submitted to him for test by any person, and to grant certificates of the results of such tests.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (38293)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Manner of test.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38293&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `All tests of petroleum made under this Act shall be made with a test apparatus`
  line `in respect of which there is valid certificate under section 16, shall have due regard to any correction`
  line `specified in that certificate, and shall be carried out in accordance with rules made under section 21.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (38294)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Certificate of testing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38294&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The testing officer after testing samples of petroleum shall make`
  line `out a certificate in the prescribed form, stating whether the petroleum is petroleum Class A or petroleum`
  line `Class B or petroleum Class C and if the petroleum is petroleum Class B or petroleum Class C, the`
  line `flash-point of the petroleum.]`
  line
  line `(2) The testing officer shall furnish the person concerned, at his request, with a certified copy of the`
  line `certificate, on payment of the prescribed fee, and such certified copy may be produced in any court in`
  line `proof of the contents of the original certificate.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) A certificate given under this section shall be admitted as evidence in any proceedings which`
  line `may be taken under this Act in respect of the petroleum from which the samples were taken, and shall,`
  line `until the contrary is proved, be conclusive proof, that the petroleum is petroleum Class A or petroleum`
  line `Class B or petroleum Class C, and, if the petroleum is petroleum Class B or petroleum Class C, of its`
  line flash-point.]
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1970, s. 13, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (38295)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Right to require re-test.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38295&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner of any petroleum, or his agent, who is dissatisfied with`
  line `the result of the test of the petroleum may, within seven days from the date on which he received`
  line `intimation of the result of the test, apply to the officer empowered under section 14 to have fresh samples`
  line `of the petroleum taken and tested.`
  line
  line `(2) On such application and on payment of the prescribed fee, fresh samples of the petroleum shall be`
  line `taken in the presence of such owner or agent or person deputed by him, and shall be tested in the presence`
  line `of such owner or agent or person deputed by him.`
  line
  line `(3) If, on such re-test, it appears that the original test was erroneous the testing officer shall cancel the`
  line `original certificate granted under section 19, shall make out a fresh certificate, and shall furnish the owner`
  line `of the petroleum, or his agent, with a certified copy thereof, free of charge.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (38296)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power to make rules regarding tests.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Governor-General-in-Council".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38296&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[Central Government] may make rules--`
  line
  line `(a) for the specification, verification, correction and replacement of the Standard Test Apparatus;`
  line
  line `(b) prescribing fees for the inspection of the Standard Test Apparatus;`
  line
  line `(c) regulating the procedure in comprising a test apparatus with the Standard Test Apparatus;`
  line
  line `(d) prescribing the form of certificate to be given in respect of a test apparatus so compared, and`
  line `the period for which such certificate shall be valid;`
  line
  line `(e) prescribing the form of the register of such certificates;`
  line
  line `(f) prescribing fees for comparing a test apparatus with Standard Test Apparatus;`
  line
  line `(g) regulating the procedure of testing officers in carrying out tests of petroleum, providing for`
  line `the averaging of results where several samples of the same petroleum are tested, and prescribing the`
  line `variations from standard temperatures which may be allowed;`
  line
  line `(h) prescribing the form of certificate of tests of petroleum and the fees which may be charged`
  line therefore;
  line
  line `(i) providing, where the results of the testing of samples raise a doubt as to the uniformity of the`
  line `quality of the petroleum in any lot under test, for the division of the lot into sub-lots, and for the`
  line `selection and testing of samples of each sub-lot and for the averaging of results in accordance with`
  line `the results of tests of those samples;`
  line
  line `(j) prescribing fees for re-tests under section 20 and providing for their refund where the original`
  line `test was erroneous; and`
  line
  line `(k) generally, regulating the procedure of all officers performing duties connected with the testing`
  line `of petroleum, and providing for any matter incidental to such testing.`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (38297)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Special rules for testing viscous or solid forms of petroleum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Governor-General-in-Council".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38297&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[Central Government]`
  line `may also make rules providing specially for the testing of any form of petroleum which is viscous or solid`
  line `or contains sediment or thickening ingredients, and such rules may modify or supplement any of the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter or of the rules made under section 21 in order to adapt them to the special`
  line `needs of such tests.`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (38298)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `General penalty for offences under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38298&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoeve--`
  line
  line `(a) in contravention of any of the provisions of Chapter I or of any of the rules made thereunder,`
  line `imports, transports, stores, produces, refines or blends any petroleum, or`
  line
  line `(b) contravenes any rule made under section 4 or section 5, or`
  line
  line `^1[(c) being the holder or a licence issued under section 4 or a person for the time being placed by`
  line `the holder of such licence in control or in charge of any place where petroleum is being imported or`
  line `stored, or is under transport, contravenes any condition of such licence or suffers any condition of`
  line `such licence to be contravened, or]`
  line
  line `(d) being for the time being in control or in charge of any place where petroleum is being`
  line `imported, stored, produced, refined or blended or is under transport, refuses or neglects to show to`
  line `any officer authorised under section 13 any receptacle, plant or appliance used in such place in`
  line `connection with petroleum, or in any way obstructs or fails to render reasonable assistance to such`
  line `officer during an inspection, or`
  line
  line `(e) being for the time being in control or in charge of any place where petroleum is being`
  line `imported, transported, stored, produced, refined or blended, refuses or neglects to show to any officer`
  line `authorised under section 14 any petroleum in such place, or to give him such assistance as he may`
  line `require for the inspection of such petroleum, or refuses to allow him to take samples of the petroleum,`
  line or
  line
  line `(f) being required, under section 27, to give information of an accident, fails to give such`
  line `information as so required by that section,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable ^2[with simple imprisonment which may extend to one month, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to one thousand rupees, or with both].`
  line
  line `(2) If any person, having been convicted of an offence punishable under sub-section (1), is again`
  line `guilty of any offence punishable under that sub-section, he shall be punishable for every such subsequent`
  line `offence ^2[with simple imprisonment which may extend to three months, or with fine which may extend to`
  line `five thousand rupees, or with both].`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1941, s. 2, for clause (c).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 24 of 1970, s. 14, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-8-1976)`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (38299)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Confiscation of petroleum and receptacles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38299&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any case in which an offence under`
  line `clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 23 has been committed, the convicting`
  line `Magistrate may direct that--`
  line
  line `(a) the petroleum in respect of which the offence has been committed, or`
  line
  line `(b) where the offender is convicted of importing, transporting or storing petroleum exceeding the`
  line `quantity he is permitted to import, transport or store, as the case may be, the whole of the petroleum`
  line `in respect of which the offence was committed,`
  line
  line `shall, together with the receptacles in which it is contained, be confiscated.`
  line
  line `(2) This power may also be exercised by the High Court in the exercise of its appellate or revisional`
  line powers.
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (38300)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title Jurisdiction.
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38300&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Offences punishable under this Act shall be triable in the Presidency-towns, by`
  line `a Presidency Magistrate, and elsewhere by a Magistrate of the first class, or by a Magistrate of the second`
  line `class who has been specially empowered by the ^32[Central Government] in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (38301)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power of entry and search.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38301&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[Central Government] may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, authorise any officer by name or by virtue of office to enter and search any place where he has`
  line `reason to believe that any petroleum is being imported, transported, stored, produced, refined or blended`
  line `otherwise than in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder, and to seize,`
  line `detain or remove any or all of the petroleum in respect of which in his opinion an offence under this Act`
  line `has been committed.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of the ^2[Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)], relating to searches shall,`
  line `so far as they are applicable, apply to searches by officers authorised under this section.`
  line
  line `(3) The ^1[Central Government] may make rules regulating the procedure of authorised officers in the`
  line `exercise of their powers under this section subject, however, to the provisions of sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Governor-General-in-Council".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 31 of 1977, s. 2, for "Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898" (w.e.f. 12-8-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (38302)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Notice of accidents with petroleum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38302&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `^1[27. Notice of accidents with petroleum.--Whenever there occurs in or about, or in connection`
  line `with, any place in which petroleum is refined, blended or kept, or any carriage or vessel either conveying`
  line `petroleum or on or from which petroleum is being loaded or unloaded, any accident by explosion`
  line `or by fire as a result of the ignition of petroleum or petroleum vapour attended with loss of human life or`
  line `serious injury to person or property, or of a description usually attended with such loss or injury, the`
  line `occupier of the place or the person for the time being in charge of the petroleum or the person in charge of`
  line `the carriage or the master of the vessel, as the case may be, shall, within such time and in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed, give notice thereof and of the attendant loss of human life, or injury to person or`
  line `property, if any, to the nearest Magistrate or to the officer in charge of the nearest police station and to`
  line `the ^2[Chief Controller of Explosives].]`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 24 of 1970, s. 15, for s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 31 of 1977, s. 2, for "Chief Inspector of Explosives in India" (w.e.f. 12-8-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (38303)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Inquiries into serious accidents with petroleum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38303&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The inquiry mentioned in section 176 of`
  line `the ^1[Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), shall, ^2[unless section 8 of the Coroners Act, 1871`
  line `(4 of 1871)], is applicable to the circumstances,] be held in all cases where any person has been killed by`
  line `an accident which the Magistrate has reason to believe was the result of the ignition of petroleum or`
  line `petroleum vapour.`
  line
  line `(2) Any Magistrate empowered to hold an inquest may also hold an inquiry under the said section`
  line `into the cause of any accident which he has reason to believe was the result of the ignition of petroleum or`
  line `petroleum vapour, if such accident was attended by serious injury to person or property, notwithstanding`
  line `that no person was killed thereby.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of ^3[sub-section (2)] a Commissioner of Police ^4*** ^5*** shall be deemed to be a`
  line `be a Magistrate empowered to hold an inquest.`
  line
  line `(4) The result of all inquiries held in pursuance of this section ^2[and of any inquiry held by a coroner`
  line `in a case to which sub-section (1) refers] shall be submitted as soon as may be to the ^6[Central`
  line Government],
  line `^2[the ^7[Chief Controller of Explosives]] and the State Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898)" (w.e.f. 12-8-1977).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 25 of 1940, s. 3.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "this section".`
  line
  line `4. The words "in a Presidency-town" omitted by Act 24 of 1970, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `5. The words "or in Rangoon" omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  line
  line `7. Subs by Act 31 of 1977, s. 4, for "Chief Inspector of Explosives in India" (w.e.f. 12-8-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (38382)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Provisions relating to rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38382&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) In making any rules under this Act, the ^1[Central Government]`
  line `Government may--`
  line
  line `(a) provide for any matter ancillary to such rules for which in ^2[its] opinion provision is necessary`
  line `necessary to protect the public from danger arising from the import, transport, storage, production,`
  line `refining or blending of petroleum, and`
  line
  line `(b) make special provision for the special circumstances of any State or place.`
  line
  line `(2) Every power to make rules conferred by this Act is subject to the condition of previous`
  line publication.
  line
  line `(3) All rules made under this Act shall be published in the Official Gazette ^3***.`
  line
  line `^4[(4) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule, or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect`
  line `only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification`
  line `or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. ibid., for "his".`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 31 of 1977, s. 5 (w.e.f. 12-8-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (38383)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title Repealed..
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465&sectionId=38383&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_32_0_000010_193430_1523351268465
